$ PHP code snippets: php_sapi_name

`php_sapi_name()` returns the name of the Server API (= SAPI) in lower case letters, such as
  • `apache`
  • `apache2handler`
  • `cgi`
  • `cgi-fcgi`
  • `cli` (for example when `php` is started as interactive shell with command line argument `-a`)
  • `cli-server`
  • `embed`
  • `fpm-fcgi`
  • `litespeed`
  • `phpdbg`


